doc.after: In 2009 researchers hypothesized that smooth edged holes found in the fossil jaws of tyrannosaurid dinosaurs such as Albertosaurus were caused by a parasite similar to Trichomonas gallinae which infects birds 49 They suggested that tyrannosaurids transmitted the infection by biting each other and that the infection impaired their ability to eat food 49
